record.title: ADJOURNMENT UNTIL 10:00 A.M. TOMORROW

speaking.paragraph: If there is no further business to come before the Senate today, I ask unanimous consent the Senate stand adjourned under the previous order.

record.narrative: There being no objection, the Senate, at 6:05 p.m., adjourned until Thursday, February 15, 2007, at 10 a.m.
